@{b}SIGN()@{ub}

Usage:@{b}SIGN(number)@{ub}

Returns 1 if the number argument is positive or zero, and -1 if number is
negative. The argument must be numeric.

Examples:
@{fg shine}
        say sign(12)                    ==>1

        say sign(-33)                   ==>-1
@{fg text}
@ENDNODE
